{"info": {"author": "Niklas Ziermann", "author_email": "n-ziermann@protonmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.4", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Topic :: Software Development :: Build Tools"], "description": "# easySocket\n\n**Version 1.0.3**\n\n\"easySocket\" is a module for Python that's based on the \"socket\" module and aims to make tasks like sending long texts or files easier/simpler.\n\nI wrote this module, because I wanted to send an image with the socket module and found it annoying to always spend multiple lines of code to be able to send an image that was bigger than the maximum amount of bytes sendable with one socket.send command.\n\n\n\n## Example\n\n```python\nimport easySocket\nc = host_tcp(\"0.0.0.0\", 8000)\neasySocket.send_file(\"./flower.png\", c)\n```\n\nThis is all you need to do to send an image file using easySocket\n\n\n\n## Install\n\n```shell\npip install easySocket\n```\n\n\n\n## Documentation\n\nHost a tcp connection with one function:\n\n```\nhost_tcp(my_ip, port)\n```\n\nConnect to a tcp conenction with one function:\t\n\n```\nconnect_tcp(ip, port)\n```\n\nSend a file over a tcp connection independent of size:\n\n```python\nsend_file(location, recipient)\n```\n\nSend a text over a tcp connection independent of size:\t\t\n\n```\nsend_text(text, recipient)\n```\n\nReceive data from one of the two functions above:\n\n```\nrcv_data(sender)\n```\n\n\n\n## Contributors\n\nNiklas Ziermann\n\n\n\n## Copyright & License\n\n**\u00a9 Niklas Ziermann** \n\n**MIT License**", "description_content_type": "", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "https://github.com/N-Ziermann/easySocket/archive/v_1.0.3.tar.gz", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/N-Ziermann/easySocket", "keywords": "socket,networking,easy,filetransfer", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "easySocket", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/easySocket/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/easySocket/", "project_urls": {"Download": "https://github.com/N-Ziermann/easySocket/archive/v_1.0.3.tar.gz", "Homepage": "https://github.com/N-Ziermann/easySocket"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/easySocket/1.0.3/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "A python module for making netwroking (especially sending files) easier", "version": "1.0.3", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <p># easySocket</p>\n<p><strong>Version 1.0.3</strong></p>\n<p>\u201ceasySocket\u201d is a module for Python that\u2019s based on the \u201csocket\u201d module and aims to make tasks like sending long texts or files easier/simpler.</p>\n<p>I wrote this module, because I wanted to send an image with the socket module and found it annoying to always spend multiple lines of code to be able to send an image that was bigger than the maximum amount of bytes sendable with one socket.send command.</p>\n<p>## Example</p>\n<p><tt>`python\nimport easySocket\nc = <span class=\"pre\">host_tcp(\"0.0.0.0\",</span> 8000)\n<span class=\"pre\">easySocket.send_file(\"./flower.png\",</span> c)\n`</tt></p>\n<p>This is all you need to do to send an image file using easySocket</p>\n<p>## Install</p>\n<p><tt>`shell\npip install easySocket\n`</tt></p>\n<p>## Documentation</p>\n<p>Host a tcp connection with one function:</p>\n<p><tt>`\nhost_tcp(my_ip, port)\n`</tt></p>\n<p>Connect to a tcp conenction with one function:</p>\n<p><tt>`\nconnect_tcp(ip, port)\n`</tt></p>\n<p>Send a file over a tcp connection independent of size:</p>\n<p><tt>`python\nsend_file(location, recipient)\n`</tt></p>\n<p>Send a text over a tcp connection independent of size:</p>\n<p><tt>`\nsend_text(text, recipient)\n`</tt></p>\n<p>Receive data from one of the two functions above:</p>\n<p><tt>`\nrcv_data(sender)\n`</tt></p>\n<p>## Contributors</p>\n<p>Niklas Ziermann</p>\n<p>## Copyright &amp; License</p>\n<p><strong>\u00a9 Niklas Ziermann</strong></p>\n<p><strong>MIT License</strong></p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6662490, "releases": {"0.0.2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "fb2b479b7af3bdd01d21830af2dd3c96", "sha256": "e85a1f287b2ce5eaab58063e45c95b48e8d5570cc30ea11ff7822a052a5516de"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "easySocket-0.0.2-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "fb2b479b7af3bdd01d21830af2dd3c96", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": null, "size": 3571, "upload_time": "2019-01-02T20:13:53", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-01-02T20:13:53.634233Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/d8/3f/c303c3b8898af386d03c104f591988a2afadc2c73e1dff5bc7e4cf74f716/easySocket-0.0.2-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "78fdc0884cab70b02d46dd7d9936d2c3", "sha256": "aa994447d22dc4aa2e56e2f7d028e4b0b88dd4905ad1bcf0f7ce7a833c1a92c1"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "easySocket-0.0.2.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "78fdc0884cab70b02d46dd7d9936d2c3", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 2326, "upload_time": "2019-01-02T20:13:55", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-01-02T20:13:55.576879Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/9c/3d/567d7ef0e7a0cb18ace88dd4c72908520171829c812258ed7da2bd5b48fe/easySocket-0.0.2.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.3": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "3c31cad94d92b108383dc8d3aad1e292", "sha256": "5c12463a9260769b28c81bbaa7716333dcf965f6eeaa061808e1b6932523354f"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "easySocket-0.0.3-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "3c31cad94d92b108383dc8d3aad1e292", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3"